title: The English seamans resolution, or, the loyall subjects undaunted valour: Plainly demonstrating the justness of his cause, incouraging [sic] his friends, to daunt his foes: for king and countrey, in the seas he'l perish, to tame the rebells, and make England flourish. To the tune of, I prethee love turn to me. Or, When this old cap was new.
publisher: Printed for F. Coles, T. Vere, and J. Wright.,
